        <p class="lead">Travel insurance serves as a crucial safety net that protects travelers from unexpected costs and provides peace of mind during adventures around the world. While no one plans for emergencies, medical issues, or trip disruptions, having appropriate coverage can mean the difference between a minor inconvenience and a financial disaster that impacts your life long after your trip ends.</p>

        <h2>Understanding Travel Insurance Basics</h2>
        <p>Travel insurance provides financial protection against various risks associated with traveling, including medical emergencies, trip cancellations, lost luggage, and other unforeseen circumstances. Policies vary significantly in coverage, cost, and terms, making it essential to understand your specific needs before purchasing.</p>

        <p>The cost of travel insurance typically ranges from 4-8% of your total trip cost, depending on coverage levels, destination, age, and trip duration. While this may seem expensive, the potential costs of medical emergencies abroad or trip cancellations often far exceed insurance premiums.</p>

        <p>Travel insurance works differently from regular health insurance, often providing primary coverage abroad and including services like emergency evacuation that domestic policies may not cover. Understanding these differences helps travelers make informed decisions about coverage needs.</p>

        <div class="post-image">
